---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout>
  <main>
    <section id="hero" class="pt-40">
      <div class="max-w-screen-2xl mx-auto px-4 md:px-12">
        <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-8xl font-heading font-light mb-8">
          Technical Requirements
        </h1>
        <p
          class="text-base md:text-lg max-w-xl mb-24 font-normal font-heading uppercase text-black/80"
        >
          Minimum Technical Requirements for running Android-based IQ-World digital signage software
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
    <section id="technical-content" class="pb-10 pt-20 max-w-screen-2xl mx-auto px-4 md:px-12">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto prose prose-lg">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">System Requirements</h2>
        
        <div class="bg-blue-50 border-l-4 border-blue-400 p-6 mb-8">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2 text-blue-800">Minimum Hardware Requirements</h3>
          <div class="text-blue-700 space-y-2">
            <p><strong>Operating System:</strong> Android</p>
            <p><strong>RAM:</strong> 1GB or more</p>
            <p><strong>Storage:</strong> 8GB or more internal storage</p>
            <p><strong>Connectivity:</strong> Wi-Fi and Ethernet</p>
            <p><strong>Bandwidth:</strong> 10 Mbps</p>
            <p><strong>USB Port:</strong> USB 2.0 or later</p>
            <p><strong>Resolution:</strong> 1366 x 768; 1920 x 1080; 3840 x 2160</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Important Considerations</h3>
        
        <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Free Hard Drive Space</h4>
        <p class="mb-6">
          For optimal performance, it is recommended that digital signage media players have sufficient free hard drive space. 
          A general guideline is to ensure that the player has between <strong>1.5 to 2 times the amount of RAM</strong> in free 
          hard drive space. This will enable the media player to operate effectively.
        </p>

        <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">GPU Performance</h4>
        <p class="mb-6">
          If you plan to play digital signage with 4K resolutions, then consider getting players with high GPU performance.
        </p>

        <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Outdoor Use</h4>
        <p class="mb-6">
          If your goal is to deploy digital signage outdoors in extreme conditions, consider setting up a cloud-based 
          digital signage system solution and having a physical network connection with the digital signage player.
        </p>

        <div class="bg-yellow-50 border-l-4 border-yellow-400 p-6 mt-8">
          <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2 text-yellow-800">Performance Tip</h4>
          <p class="text-yellow-700">
            For best results with 4K content, ensure your hardware exceeds the minimum requirements and has dedicated GPU capabilities.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-gray-100 p-6 rounded-lg mt-8">
          <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">Technical Support</h4>
          <p>
            Need help determining if your hardware meets these requirements? Contact our technical team at 
            <a href="mailto:sales@cansignage.com" class="text-blue-600 underline">sales@cansignage.com</a> 
            or call <strong>+91 91523 98498</strong>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>